         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="0012_002414_000229_0001.jpg" xml:id="d4e39"/>
            <p>Joseph Ball Esqr</p>
            <p>President Ins Co. N. A.</p>
            <p>Letter</p>
            <p>Dr. J. Mease</p>
            <p>June 18, 1799.</p>
            <pb n="2" facs="0012_002414_000229_0002.jpg" xml:id="d4e51"/>
            <p>Philadelphia June 17th, 1799.</p>
            <p>Sir</p>
            <p>The time for which I rented the office adjoining the insurance office from you, will expire on the 27
				       <unclear reason="illegible" resp="pw">snst</unclear>.  I think the present rent of Â£50. is
				       much too high, considering the present state of affairs, and the universal<unclear reason="illegible" resp="pw">depicinution</unclear>
				       of the value of houses in the City: and as I have no doubt they will experience a further fall, I propose
				       to you to <unclear reason="illegible" resp="pw">latas</unclear>the office for another year at one
				       hundred dollars.</p>
            <p>with respect</p>
            <p>I am Sir</p>
            <p>your friend</p>
            <p>Jas. Mease</p>
            <p>J. Ball Esqr</p>
            <p>Prest. Ins. Co. N. A.</p>
         </div>
